When clicking the play button, the default media player is usually started.
With this option enabled, the directory of the media file is first checked for a file
with the same name as the media file, but ending in \"xmm.sh\" or \"xmm.bat\". If such a file exists,
the file content will be executed as it would be done on the command line. If no such file
is found, the media player will be executed instead.
